Andrew Steele had pleaded not guilty by reason of mental disease to two counts of first-degree intentional homicide in the August 22 shooting deaths of his wife and sister-in-law . 
  His wife Ashlee Steele and her sister Kacee Tollefsbol were found dead of gunshot wounds at Steele's home in Fitchburg, Wisconsin . 
  Defense attorneys argued that Lou Gehrig's disease had damaged Steele's brain, making him not criminally responsible for the deaths . 
  A jury found him not legally responsible on Thursday . 
  Steele had written a rambling note the day before the killings claiming he had sex with the women . 
  He had been diagnosed with the disease in June . 
